# Homelab — Project Brief

## What This Is
A personal home platform (homelab) running on a local network (Raspberry Pi), built by a software engineer as both a useful home tool and a portfolio piece demonstrating full-stack skills: frontend, backend, database, CI/CD, Docker, Ansible, and more.

**Users:** household members + anyone on the local network. No auth required initially.

## End Goal
A single local domain serving multiple modules as separate routes/sections:
- `/recipes` — Recipe manager with a weekly randomizer
- More to come — this is an evolving platform

## Tech Stack & Decisions

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | React + TypeScript + Vite | Adds React to portfolio (Angular already used at day job) |
| Backend | Spring Boot + Spring Data JPA + Flyway | Simpler than manual Jetty/Guice/MyBatis stack — comparison between the two is an interview talking point |
| Database | PostgreSQL | Relational, robust, already familiar |
| Containers | Docker + Docker Compose | Most recognized, community resources |
| Reverse Proxy | Nginx | Routes modules by path under one local domain |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions + self-hosted runner on Pi | Free, widely recognized by employers, Pi does the actual build/deploy |
| Deployment | Ansible | Provisions and deploys to Raspberry Pi |
| Repo style | Monorepo | All modules under one repo |

## Repository Structure
```
homelab/
├── frontend/           # React + TypeScript + Vite
├── backend/            # Spring Boot API
├── infra/
│   ├── ansible/        # Pi provisioning + deployment playbooks
│   └── docker/         # Docker Compose files
└── .github/
    └── workflows/      # GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines
```

## Key Constraints
- **Local network only** for now (may go public later — design with that possibility in mind)
- **All tools must be free / open source**
- **Runs on Raspberry Pi** (ARM architecture — ensure Docker images are multi-arch or ARM-compatible)
- No authentication required initially

